WITH date_gen AS (
    





with rawdata as (

    

    

    with p as (
        select 0 as generated_number union all select 1
    ), unioned as (

    select

    
    p0.generated_number * power(2, 0)
     + 
    
    p1.generated_number * power(2, 1)
     + 
    
    p2.generated_number * power(2, 2)
     + 
    
    p3.generated_number * power(2, 3)
     + 
    
    p4.generated_number * power(2, 4)
     + 
    
    p5.generated_number * power(2, 5)
     + 
    
    p6.generated_number * power(2, 6)
     + 
    
    p7.generated_number * power(2, 7)
     + 
    
    p8.generated_number * power(2, 8)
     + 
    
    p9.generated_number * power(2, 9)
     + 
    
    p10.generated_number * power(2, 10)
     + 
    
    p11.generated_number * power(2, 11)
    
    
    + 1
    as generated_number

    from

    
    p as p0
     cross join 
    
    p as p1
     cross join 
    
    p as p2
     cross join 
    
    p as p3
     cross join 
    
    p as p4
     cross join 
    
    p as p5
     cross join 
    
    p as p6
     cross join 
    
    p as p7
     cross join 
    
    p as p8
     cross join 
    
    p as p9
     cross join 
    
    p as p10
     cross join 
    
    p as p11
    
    

    )

    select *
    from unioned
    where generated_number <= 2192
    order by generated_number



),

all_periods as (

    select (
        

    dateadd(
        day,
        row_number() over (order by 1) - 1,
        cast('2019-01-01' as date)
        )


    ) as date_day
    from rawdata

),

filtered as (

    select *
    from all_periods
    where date_day <= cast('2025-01-01' as date)

)

select * from filtered


),
company_gen AS (
     SELECT 'MSFT' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'GOG' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'AMZN' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'A' AS company_name
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 'FB' AS company_name
),
country_gen AS (
    SELECT 'FR' AS country
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 'DE' AS country
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 'GB' AS country
    UNION ALL
    SELECT 'US' AS country
    UNION all

)

FROM date_gen, company_gen, country_gen

WITH  raw_data AS (
    SELECT
        DISTINCT
        company_name
        , country
        , CAST(date_trunc('month', date_day) AS Date) AS date_month
    FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_generator
),
missing_month AS (
    SELECT * FROM raw_data
    WHERE NOT (
        
        (company_name = 'FB' AND country = 'CA' AND date_month BETWEEN DATE('2019-05-01') AND DATE('2019-07-05')) OR
        (company_name = 'GOOG' AND country = 'FR' AND date_month BETWEEN DATE('2020-01-01') AND DATE('2020-05-01')) OR
        (company_name = 'AAPL' AND country = 'US' AND date_month BETWEEN DATE('2021-05-15') AND DATE('2021-12-26')) OR
        
        (date_month  BETWEEN DATE('2022-05-01') AND DATE('2022-08-05')) OR
        
        (country = 'DE' AND date_month BETWEEN DATE('2019-09-07') AND DATE('2019-11-09')) OR
        
        (company_name = 'AMZN' AND date_month BETWEEN DATE('2019-01-07') AND DATE('2019-09-09'))
    )
)
SELECT * FROM missing_month

SELECT
    country
    , SUM(str_length) AS sum_2_str_length
    -- example: sum
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS sum_percent

    , COUNT(company_name) AS count_company_name
    -- example: count
    -- defaults to count if no aggregation function is specified and 1 decimal if no precision is specified

    , 




    ROUND(
      
        COUNT(company_name)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent

    , COUNT(DISTINCT company_name) AS count_distinct_company_name
    -- example: countdistinct
    , 




    ROUND(
      
      COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS count_distinct_percent

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1
ORDER BY sum(str_length)  DESC

SELECT
    company_name
    , country
    , count(str_length) AS count_str_length
    -- the percentages are caclulated at the aggregation of company_name and not entire column
    , 



  


    ROUND(
      
        count(str_length)
        /
        SUM(count(str_length)) OVER (PARTITION BY company_name)
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1,2
ORDER BY company_name, country, count(str_length)  DESC

WITH
percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
        company_name
        , country
        , 




    ROUND(
      
        COUNT(str_length)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent
        , 



  


    ROUND(
      
        COUNT(str_length)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(str_length)) OVER (PARTITION BY company_name)
      
    , 3)
 AS count_percent_level

    FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
    GROUP BY 1,2
    ORDER BY company_name, country, sum(str_length)  DESC
)
SELECT * FROM percent_of_total
WHERE
    1=1
    -- aggregated percent at level is always greater than percent of entire column
    AND count_percent_level > count_percent
    -- MSFT has 3 countries, so each should be 1/3 of the total
    AND company_name = 'MSFT' AND count_percent_level <> .333
    -- AMZN & FB are unfiltered and have 5 countries, so each should be 1/5 of the total
    AND company_name IN ('AMZN','FB') AND count_percent_level <> .2
    -- Each with 4 countries, so each should be 1/4 of the total
    AND company_name IN ('GOG','A') AND count_percent_level <> .25

WITH
percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
    country
    -- rounding defaults to 1 if unspecified
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 2)
 AS sum_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 2)
 AS sum_percent_3

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1
)
SELECT * FROM percent_of_total
WHERE
    country = 'GB'
    AND sum_percent <> 0.2
    AND sum_percent <> 0.24

WITH
percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
    country
    -- precision needs to be atleast 4 for the sum to be 100%
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        sum(str_length)
        /
        SUM(sum(str_length)) OVER ()
      
    , 4)
 AS sum_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        count(company_name)
        /
        SUM(count(company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 4)
 AS count_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
      COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)
        /
        SUM(COUNT(DISTINCT company_name)) OVER ()
      
    , 4)
 AS count_distinct_percent
    , 




    ROUND(
      
        NULL
      
    , 2)
 AS incorrect_returns_null

FROM dbt_db.dbt_schema.data_aggregated
GROUP BY 1
)
, sum_percent_of_total AS (
    SELECT
        sum(sum_percent) AS sum_percent
        , sum(count_percent) AS count_percent
        , sum(count_distinct_percent) AS count_distinct_percent
        , sum(incorrect_returns_null) AS incorrect_returns_null
    FROM percent_of_total
)
SELECT * FROM sum_percent_of_total
WHERE
    sum_percent<>1
    OR count_percent<>1
    OR count_distinct_percent<>1
    OR incorrect_returns_null IS NOT NULL

            (company_name) DESC,
        
        date_day DESC) AS next_date_day
  FROM unique_dates
)
SELECT
    date_day
    
        , (country) AS country
    
        , (company_name) AS company_name
    
    , next_date_day
    , ABS(datediff(
        DAY,
        next_date_day,
        date_day
        )) AS missing_day
FROM dates_lagged
WHERE datediff(
        DAY,
        next_date_day,
        date_day
        ) < -1


)
, row_count_missing_values AS (
    SELECT COUNT(missing_day) AS row_count
    FROM missing_values
)
-- Only rows corresponding to company A are picked up as the str_length is set to 3
SELECT * FROM row_count_missing_values WHERE row_count <> 3
